'''Sebastián Andrés Beccacece''' (born 17 December 1980) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|football]] [[Manager (association football)|manager]]. He is the current head coach of the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Personal life==
Born in [[Rosario]], Beccacece lived in the La República neighborhood with his parents Julio and Mónica, and his two brothers. His [[twin]] brother Aníbal played football for their hometown side [[Central Córdoba de Rosario|Central Córdoba]].<ref name="ELG">{{cite web|url=https://www.elgrafico.com.ar/articulo/1089/17408/quien-es-como-se-forma-y-como-piensa-sebastian-beccacece|title=Quién es, cómo se forma y cómo piensa Sebastián Beccacece|trans-title=Who is, how sets out and how thinks Sebastián Beccacece|publisher=[[El Gráfico (Argentina)|El Gráfico]]|language=es|date=12 December 2016|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

==Career==
===Early career===
Beccacece played for Argentine amateur clubs Lavalle and Juan XXIII as a right back when he was teenager,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.revistacabal.coop/deportes/entrevista-sebastian-beccacece|title=Entrevista a Sebastián Beccacece|trans-title=Interview to Sebastián Beccacece|publisher=Revista Cabal|language=es|date=5 July 2017|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> but after realising he would not become a top-tier footballer, he stopped playing.<ref name="ELG"/> He then started working at [[Newell's Old Boys]]' youth setup, initially managing kids between the age of four and 12. He also worked at Club Renato Cesarini's youth setup, managing the 1989/1990 age groups.<ref name="AyP">{{cite web|url=http://www.azulyplomo.com/noticias/ultimasNoticias/index.php?noticiaID=4719|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120303101505/http://www.azulyplomo.com/noticias/ultimasNoticias/index.php?noticiaID=4719|title="Jorge Sampaoli se la jugó por mí"|trans-title="Jorge Sampaoli took a bet on me"|publisher=Azul y Plomo|language=es|date=16 July 2010|archivedate=3 March 2012|url-status=usurped|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

===Working with Sampaoli===
After meeting [[Jorge Sampaoli]] in his hometown in 2002, Beccacece was named his assistant coach at Peruvian side [[Sport Boys]] in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emelec.com.ec/2010/11/perfiles-electricos-sebastian-beccacece/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213111209/http://www.emelec.com.ec/2010/11/perfiles-electricos-sebastian-beccacece/|title=Perfiles Eléctricos: Sebastián Beccacece|publisher=CS Emelec|language=es|date=16 November 2010|archivedate=13 December 2013|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> He remained his assistant at [[Coronel Bolognesi]] (2004–2005 and 2006), [[Sporting Cristal]] (2007), [[Club Deportivo O'Higgins|O'Higgins]] (2008–2009) and [[Club Sport Emelec|Emelec]] (2010).<ref>{{cite web |title=Los entrenadores que partieron como ayudantes |url=https://chile.as.com/chile/2015/11/24/album/1448387872_150049.html |website=[[Diario AS]] |access-date=5 February 2026 |language=es |date=25 November 2015}}</ref>

[[File:Universidad de Chile, campeón Copa Sudamericana 2011, en La Moneda.jpg|thumb|left|Beccacece (first row, fifth from left) with Universidad de Chile's [[2011 Copa Sudamericana]] champion team at [[Palacio de la Moneda|Moneda Palace]] with the then president [[Sebastián Piñera]].]]
In 2010, following the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]], Beccacece reportedly rejected an invitation of [[Marcelo Bielsa]] to work as his assistant in the [[Chile national football team|Chile national team]], and continued to work with Sampaoli.<ref name="AyP"/> The duo subsequently joined [[Club Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]] for the 2011 season, where they won the [[2011 Torneo Apertura (Chile)|2011 Apertura]], the [[2011 Torneo Clausura (Chile)|2011 Clausura]], the [[2012 Torneo Apertura (Chile)|2012 Apertura]] and the [[2011 Copa Sudamericana]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2011/10/20/508908/universidad-de-chile-y-las-razones-de-su-increible-presente.html|title=Universidad de Chile y las razones de su increíble presente|trans-title=Universidad de Chile and the reasons for their incredible present|newspaper=El Mercurio|language=es|date=20 December 2011|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref>

Following their success at Universidad de Chile, in 2013, Beccacece and Sampaoli were signed by the [[ANFP]] to led the Chile national team, finally arriving there after rejecting Bielsa's offer.<ref>{{cite web|work=El Gráfico Chile|title=El carismático cuerpo técnico que acompañará a Sampaoli en la Roja|trans-title=The charismatic staff who will follow Sampaoli in ''la Roja''|url=http://www.elgraficochile.cl/el-carismatico-cuerpo-tecnico-que-acompanara-a-sampaoli-en-la-roja/prontus_elgrafico/2012-12-03/145959.html|language=es|date=3 December 2012|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref> At Chile they achieved the qualification to the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] and lifted the first ever [[2015 Copa América|Copa América title]] in the country's history. In 2015, they resigned from the Chile national team amidst the [[2015 FIFA corruption case|FIFA corruption case]] where they were involved alongside the federation's president [[Sergio Jadue]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[La Nación (Chile)|La Nación]]|title=ANFP acudirá a la FIFA por demanda de Sebastián Beccacece|trans-title=The ANFP will resort to FIFA due to Sebastián Beccacece's lawsuit|url=http://www.lanacion.cl/noticias/deportes/futbol-nacional/anfp-acudira-a-la-fifa-por-demanda-de-sebastian-beccacece/2016-07-13/110944.html|language=es|date=13 July 2016|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref>

===Universidad de Chile===
On 11 January 2016, Beccacece ended his spell as Sampaoli's assistant to take over Universidad de Chile, replacing [[Martín Lasarte]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[El Mercurio|Emol]]|title=Sebastián Beccacece fue presentado en la U y aclaró ‘error’ que cometió con Martín Lasarte|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece was presented in ''la U'' and clarified the 'error' they committed with Martín Lasarte|language=es|url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/Deportes/2016/01/11/767932/Sebastian-Beccacece-fue-presentado-en-la-U-y-aclaro-error-que-cometio-con-Martin-Lasarte.html|date=11 January 2016|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref> During his first days at the club, the team received as signings the Argentine playmaker [[Luis Fariña]] on 12 January,<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=Luis Fariña aprueba exámenes y Monzón se acerca a la U|url=http://chile.as.com/chile/2016/01/11/futbol/1452552028_426027.html|date=12 January 2016|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref> and a week later, the Chilean international [[Gonzalo Jara (footballer, born 1985)|Gonzalo Jara]]<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Canal 13 (Chile)|T13.cl]]|title=Gonzalo Jara ya entrena junto a Universidad de Chile|url=http://www.t13.cl/noticia/deportes13/futbol-nacional/gonzalo-jara-ya-entrena-junto-universidad-chile|date=19 January 2016|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref> and the also Argentine [[Fabián Monzón]] from [[Calcio Catania|Catania]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=Monzón destraba su situación y será el tercer refuerzo de la U|url=http://www.latercera.com/noticia/deportes/2016/01/656-664889-9-monzon-destraba-su-situacion-y-sera-el-tercer-refuerzo-de-la-u.shtml|date=19 January 2016|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref>

On 24 January, in his second [[2016 Torneo Clausura (Chile)|league game]] since his debut for this competition at the bench (a 1–1 away draw with [[Deportes Antofagasta]]), Beccacece impressed following the team's 8–1 home thrash over [[O'Higgins F.C.|O'Higgins]] at the [[Estadio Nacional Julio Martínez Prádanos|Estadio Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=La U es pura fiesta y humilla a O'Higgins en el Nacional|url=http://chile.as.com/chile/2016/01/24/futbol/1453658484_125978.html|date=24 January 2016|access-date=7 September 2016}}</ref> After of that great victory nevertheless the team reaped three draws and one loss against [[CD Palestino|Palestino]] (2–1). During February's first days, the team was eliminated of the [[2016 Copa Libertadores first stage|Copa Libertadores first stage]] by Uruguay's [[River Plate F.C.|River Plate]], which was his first failure and it meant being the target of criticism from the press and the team's supporters.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[El Universo]]|title=River Plate de Uruguay elimina a Universidad de Chile y avanza en Copa Libertadores|url=http://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/2016/02/10/nota/5396575/river-plate-uruguay-elimina-universidad-chile-avanza-copa|date=10 February 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> On 28 February, the 4–1 away victory over [[Cobresal]] would be a balm of the team's moment.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=La U golea a Cobresal en el norte y Beccacece respira|url=http://chile.as.com/chile/2016/02/28/futbol/1456688319_970740.html|date=28 February 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> Following a 0–0 draw with [[Unión Española]] and two losses (3–1 with [[Club Deportivo Universidad de Concepción|Universidad de Concepción]] as local and 5–4 against [[Santiago Wanderers]] as visitors), he back to draw, now in the [[Chilean football derby]] with [[Colo-Colo]], which was again a goalless where both teams were criticized for its game level.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=La U y Colo Colo igualan en un Superclásico para el olvido|url=http://chile.as.com/chile/2016/03/20/futbol/1458484444_046128.html|date=21 March 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> Finally, Beccacece would end in the tenth place with three wins, seven draws and five losses and his continuity was heavily questioned during the [[2016 Copa América Centenario|Copa América Centenario]] break.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=Heller ratifica a Beccacece como DT de la U, pero aclara que se irá a fin de año si vuelve a fracasar|url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/Deportes/2016/05/11/802330/Heller-ratifica-a-Beccacece-como-DT-de-la-U.html|date=11 May 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref>

For the purpose of the 2016 Torneo Apertura, the club hired to Luis María Bonini as fitness coach<ref>{{cite web|work=[[La Tercera]]|title=Comienza la era Bonini en la U de Beccacece|url=http://www.latercera.com/noticia/deportes/2016/05/656-681873-9-comienza-la-era-bonini-en-la-u-de-beccacece.shtml|date=23 May 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> and were appointed ten players which joined the club, between the most important figured [[Jean Beausejour]] from archi-rivals Colo-Colo, [[Christian Vilches]] from [[Atlético Paranaense]] (former Colo-Colo too) and the Argentine playmaker [[Gastón Fernández]] from [[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[AS (newspaper)|AS Chile]]|title=¡Fin de la película! Universidad de Chile selló finalmente a su último refuerzo|url=http://www.elperiscopio.cl/2016/07/27/admin/fin-de-la-pelicula-universidad-de-chile-sello-finalmente-a-su-ultimo-refuerzo/|date=27 July 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> He began the tournament losing 1–0 with Wanderers at [[Valparaíso]], and drawing 1–1 as locals with Deportes Antofagasta on 7 August, date where again his continuity was questioned.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Canal 13 (Chile)|T13.cl]]|title=Dirigencia de Azul Azul confirma continuidad de Beccacece en el banco de la ‘U’|url=http://www.t13.cl/noticia/deportes13/futbol-nacional/dirigencia-azul-azul-confirma-continuidad-beccacece-banco-u|date=8 August 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> Nevertheless, he would return to victory, reaching two consecutive triumphs with [[San Luis de Quillota]] (4–2) and Universidad de Concepción (3–1), that this time saw their end on 27 August after being defeated 3–0 by [[Club Deportivo Universidad Católica|Universidad Católica]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Universidad de Chile|Radio Universidad de Chile]]|title=Universidad Católica golea a la ‘U’ de Beccacece|url=http://radio.uchile.cl/2016/08/27/universidad-catolica-golea-a-la-u-de-beccacece/|date=8 August 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref> Highlighting, that game he kicked a freezer next to the bench during the moment that the referee Roberto Tobar took penalty which finally was Católica's third goal.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Universidad de Chile|Radio Universidad de Chile]]|title=Beccacece explicó su airada reacción: ‘Son impulsos que son desmedidos y no deben suceder’|url=http://www.elgraficochile.cl/beccacece-explico-su-airada-reaccion-son-impulsos-que-son-desmedidos-y/prontus_elgrafico/2016-08-27/142421.html|date=27 August 2016|access-date=9 September 2016}}</ref>

Beccacece left ''la U'' on 17 September 2016, after agreeing to cut short his contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.biobiochile.cl/noticias/deportes/futbol/universidad-de-chile/2016/09/17/no-va-mas-sebastian-beccacece-dejara-de-ser-el-entrenador-de-universidad-de-chile.shtml|title=Se acabó: Sebastián Beccacece dejará de ser el entrenador de Universidad de Chile|trans-title=It is done: Sebastián Beccacece will stop being the manager of Universidad de Chile|publisher=[[Radio Bío-Bío]]|language=es|date=17 September 2016|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

===Defensa y Justicia===
On 15 November 2016, Beccacece replaced [[Ariel Holan]] at the helm of [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Defensa y Justicia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/448|title=Sebastián Beccacece nuevo entrenador de Defensa y Justicia|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece new manager of Defensa y Justicia|publisher=Defensa y Justicia|language=es|date=15 November 2016|accessdate=10 February 2021}}</ref> His first match in charge of the club occurred thirteen days later, a 1–2 loss against [[Club Atlético Patronato|Patronato]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.t13.cl/noticia/deportes13/futbol-internacional/beccacece-tuvo-amargo-debut-dos-minutos-pierde-su-estreno-defensa-y-justicia|title=Beccacece tuvo un amargo debut: En dos minutos pierde en su estreno con Defensa y Justicia|trans-title=Beccacece had a bitter debut: Within two minutes he lost in his debut with Defensa y Justicia|publisher=[[Teletrece]]|language=es|date=28 November 2016|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

Beccacece was also in charge of Defensa during their [[2017 Copa Sudamericana]] run, the club's first continental competition in their history, where they notably knocked out Brazilian side [[São Paulo FC|São Paulo]] at the [[Morumbi Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.t13.cl/noticia/deportes13/futbol-internacional/defensa-y-justicia-sebastian-beccacece-elimina-sao-paulo-sudamericana|title=Defensa y Justicia de Sebastián Beccacece elimina Sao Paulo de la Sudamericana|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece's Defensa y Justicia knock out São Paulo from the Sudamericana|publisher=Teletrece|language=es|date=12 May 2017|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> His last match in charge occurred on 28 June, a 1–0 win against [[Associação Chapecoense de Futebol|Chapecoense]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chile.as.com/chile/2017/06/29/futbol/1498736435_247616.html|title=Beccacece: "Fue un final soñado con Defensa y Justicia"|trans-title=Beccacece: "It was a dream ending with Defensa y Justicia"|publisher=Diario AS|language=es|date=29 June 2017|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> as he left the club to join Sampaoli's staff again.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elgrafico.com.ar/articulo/1066/24728/defensa-despide-a-beccacece|title=Defensa despide a Beccacece|trans-title=Defensa sack Beccacece|publisher=El Gráfico|language=es|date=28 June 2017|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

===Argentina (assistant)===
After admitting contacts made by Sampaoli in April 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/seleccion-nacional/sebastian-beccacece-reconocio-sampaoli-llamo-ir-seleccion-pensarlo_0_rJecnEZ1W.html|title=Sebastián Beccacece reconoció que Sampaoli lo llamó para ir a la Selección: "Tengo que pensarlo"|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece recognized that Sampaoli called him to go to the national team: "I have to think about it"|publisher=[[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]]|language=es|date=28 April 2017|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> Beccacece accepted the role as his assistant manager at the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina football team]] in May,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es/noticias/beccacece-acepto-acompanar-a-sampaoli-a-un-hermano-no-se-le/zy3wfngpg7t013bxyyzh0il1b|title=Beccacece aceptó acompañar a Sampaoli: "A un hermano no se le puede decir que no"|trans-title=Beccacece accepted to join Sampaoli: "You cannot say no to a brother"|publisher=Goal.com|language=es|date=23 May 2017|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> and joined the staff in June. Despite struggling in the qualifiers, they achieved the qualification to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in the last round.

After Argentina's elimination from the World Cup, Beccacece rescinded his contract with the [[Argentine Football Association]] on 6 July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/mundial-2018/2018/07/06/es-oficial-sebastian-beccacece-dejo-a-jorge-sampaoli-y-se-alejo-de-la-seleccion-argentina/|title=Es oficial: Sebastián Beccacece dejó a Jorge Sampaoli y se alejó de la selección argentina|trans-title=It is official: Sebastián Beccacece left Jorge Sampaoli and got farther from the Argentina national team|publisher=[[Infobae]]|language=es|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

===Defensa y Justicia return===
On 7 July 2018, Beccacece returned to Defensa y Justicia, again being named their manager.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://argentina.as.com/argentina/2018/07/07/futbol/1530972475_252216.html|title=Sebastián Beccacece vuelve a Defensa y Justicia|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece returns to Defensa y Justicia|publisher=Diario AS|language=es|date=7 July 2018|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> He achieved an impressive [[2018–19 Argentine Primera División|2018–19 season]] with the club, finishing second and qualifying the team to the [[Copa Libertadores]] for the first time in their history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prensafutbol.cl/281517-historico-beccacece-clasifico-defensa-y-justicia-libertadores/|title=Beccacece histórico: Defensa por primera vez a Copa Libertadores|trans-title=Historical Beccacece: Defensa for the first time in the Copa Libertadores|publisher=Prensa Fútbol|language=es|date=12 March 2019|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

===Independiente===
On 7 June 2019, Beccacece was presented as manager of fellow top-tier side [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2019/06/07/sebastian-beccacece-fue-presentado-como-nuevo-entrenador-de-independiente-quienes-son-los-tres-primeros-refuerzos-que-contacto/|title=Sebastián Beccacece fue presentado como nuevo entrenador de Independiente: quiénes son los tres primeros refuerzos que contactó|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece was presented as new manager of Independiente: who are the first three additions that he contacted|publisher=Infobae|language=es|date=7 June 2019|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> He left the club on 26 October, by mutual agreement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.ar/futbol/argentina/nota/_/id/6242333/beccacece-dejo-de-ser-el-tecnico-de-independiente|title=Beccacece dejó de ser el técnico de Independiente|trans-title=Beccacece left as manager of Independiente|publisher=[[ESPN]]|language=es|date=26 October 2019|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref>

===Racing Club===
On 16 December 2019, Beccacece signed an 18-month contract with [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]], still in the Argentine top tier.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2019/12/16/sebastian-beccacece-es-el-nuevo-tecnico-de-racing-firma-contrato-por-18-meses/|title=Sebastián Beccacece es el nuevo técnico de Racing: firma contrato por 18 meses|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece is the new manager of Racing: signs contract for 18 months|publisher=Infobae|language=es|date=16 December 2019|accessdate=11 February 2021}}</ref> He led the club to a fourth position in [[2019–20 Argentine Primera División|the league]] before its abandonment due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], and reached the quarterfinals of the [[2020 Copa Libertadores]] before being knocked out by [[Boca Juniors]].

On 26 December 2020, Beccacece resigned.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-12/27/c_139621261.htm |title=Coach of Argentina's Racing Club announces departure |website=Xinhua |date=26 December 2020 |access-date=27 January 2021}}</ref>

===Defensa y Justicia (3rd spell)===
On 15 February 2021, Beccacece returned to Defensa for a third spell.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defensayjusticia.org.ar/noticias/1565|title=Comienza el tercer ciclo de Sebastián Beccacece en la institución|trans-title=Begins the third spell of Sebastián Beccacece in the institution|publisher=Defensa y Justicia|language=es|date=15 February 2021|accessdate=17 February 2021}}</ref> He resigned on 11 September of the following year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tycsports.com/liga-profesional-de-futbol/sebastian-beccacece-defensa-y-justicia-id463281.html |title=Sebastián Beccacece se va de Defensa y Justicia: "Es el momento indicado para irme" |trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece leaves Defensa y Justicia: "It is the right moment to leave"|date=8 September 2022 |publisher=[[TyC Sports]] |language=Spanish}}</ref>

===Elche===
On 21 March 2023, Beccacece was named in charge of Spanish [[La Liga]] side [[Elche CF|Elche]], becoming their fourth manager of [[2022–23 La Liga|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elchecf.es/noticia/oficial-sebastian-beccacece-nuevo-entrenador-del-elche-c-f|title=OFICIAL {{!}} Sebastián Beccacece, nuevo entrenador del Elche C.F.|trans-title=OFFICIAL {{!}} Sebastián Beccacece, new manager of Elche C.F.|publisher=Elche CF|language=es|date=21 March 2023|accessdate=21 March 2023|archive-date=21 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230321144347/https://www.elchecf.es/noticia/oficial-sebastian-beccacece-nuevo-entrenador-del-elche-c-f|url-status=dead}}</ref> Despite suffering relegation, he remained in charge of the club in [[2023–24 Segunda División|the following campaign]], before announcing his departure on 26 May 2024, after the club's chances to qualify to [[2024 Segunda División play-offs|the play-offs]] were extinguished.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/espana/nota/_/id/13710502/sebastian-beccacece-anuncio-que-dejara-elche-al-final-de-la-temporada|title=Sebastián Beccacece anunció que dejará Elche al final de la temporada|trans-title=Sebastián Beccacece announced that he will leave Elche at the end of the season|publisher=[[ESPN Deportes]]|language=es|date=26 May 2024|accessdate=16 June 2024}}</ref>

=== Ecuador ===
On 1 August 2024, he was announced as head coach of the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/la-tri/sebastian-beccacece-nuevo-entrenador-ecuador-seleccion-oficial-tri_0_tWBy8dVpvW.html|title=Es oficial: Sebastián Beccacece, nuevo entrenador de la Selección de Ecuador|access-date=1 August 2024|last=|first=|date=1 August 2024|publisher=Olé Ecuador|language=es-EC}}</ref>

